<subSubSection id="C3485ED60948B216ECC5FD9A20DC493C" pageId="28" pageNumber="479" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BED0D5D0948B216ECC5FD9A24CC48E4" blockId="28.[151,1437,150,789]" pageId="28" pageNumber="479">
<emphasis id="B926D14F0948B216ECC5FD9A21594849" bold="true" box="[199,338,582,608]" pageId="28" pageNumber="479">Comments:</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFC370AC0948B216ED59FD9B224F4848" author="Kottelat, M." box="[347,580,583,609]" pageId="28" pageNumber="479" pagination="1 - 663" refId="ref24453" refString="Kottelat, M. (2013) The fishes of the inland waters of southeast Asia: a catalogue and core bibliography of the fishes known to occur in freshwaters, mangroves and estuaries. Raffles Bulletin of Zoology, Supplement 27, 1 - 663." type="journal article" year="2013">Kottelat (2013: 394)</bibRefCitation>
used the combination 
<taxonomicName id="4C5276DE0948B216EF49FD9B24694848" authorityName="Valenciennes" authorityYear="1837" box="[843,1122,583,609]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Eleotridae" genus="Ophiocara" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="28" pageNumber="479" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="ophicephalus">
<emphasis id="B926D14F0948B216EF49FD9B24694848" box="[843,1122,583,609]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="479">Ophiocara ophicephalus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
recognizing as first reviser 
<bibRefCitation id="EFC370AC0948B216EC95FDB7217748AC" author="Gunther, A." box="[151,380,619,645]" pageId="28" pageNumber="479" refId="ref23877" refString="Gunther, A. (1861) Catalogue of the Acanthopterygian Fishes in the Collection of the British Museum. British Museum (Natural History), London, 586 pp. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 8809" type="book" year="1861">Günther (1861: 107)</bibRefCitation>
who gave precedence to 
<taxonomicName id="4C5276DE0948B216EE91FDB7232348AC" authorityName="Valenciennes" authorityYear="1837" box="[659,808,619,645]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Eleotridae" genus="Ophiocara" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="28" pageNumber="479" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="ophicephalus">
<emphasis id="B926D14F0948B216EE91FDB7232348AC" box="[659,808,619,645]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="479">ophicephalus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
over 
<taxonomicName id="4C5276DE0948B216EF65FDB723F848AC" authorityName="Valenciennes" authorityYear="1837" box="[871,1011,619,645]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Eleotridae" genus="Eleotris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="28" pageNumber="479" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="porocephala">
<emphasis id="B926D14F0948B216EF65FDB723F848AC" box="[871,1011,619,645]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="479">porocephala</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Treated as 
<taxonomicName id="4C5276DE0948B216E87AFDB7252C48AC" authorityName="Valenciennes" authorityYear="1837" box="[1144,1319,619,645]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Eleotridae" genus="Eleotris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="28" pageNumber="479" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="porocephala">
<emphasis id="B926D14F0948B216E87AFDB7252C48AC" box="[1144,1319,619,645]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="479">O. porocephala</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by 
<bibRefCitation id="EFC370AC0948B216E94CFDB721294880" author="Larson, H. K. &amp; Ravelomanana, T. &amp; Sparks, J. S." pageId="28" pageNumber="479" pagination="58335116" refId="ref24686" refString="Larson, H. K., Ravelomanana, T. &amp; Sparks, J. S. (2017). Ophiocara porocephala. The IUCN Red List of Threatened Species, 2017, e. T 188101 A 58335116." type="journal article" year="2017">
Larson 
<emphasis id="B926D14F0948B216EC95FD5320DB4880" box="[151,208,655,681]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="479">et al.</emphasis>
(2017)
</bibRefCitation>
and by an overwhelming number of ichthyologists in recent and past literature. The taxonomy of this species has never been reviewed and it may represent more than one species (see 
<bibRefCitation id="EFC370AC0948B216E82AFD6F24B148E4" author="Parenti, P." box="[1064,1210,691,717]" pageId="28" pageNumber="479" pagination="1 - 480" refId="ref25048" refString="Parenti, P. (2021) A checklist of the gobioid fishes of the world (Percomorpha: Gobiiformes). Iranian Journal of Ichthyology, 8, 1 - 480." type="journal article" year="2021">Parenti 2021</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
